OL,3,CMillions of workers to get new rights
OL,4,Cfrom day one in job under new law
OL,6,FCurrently for example, workers have to
OL,7,Fbe in a job for two years before they
OL,8,Fcan have a case for unfair dismissal,
OL,9,Fbut under the new plans workers will
OL,10,Fhave the right from day one.
OL,12,FMinisters have described it as the
OL,13,Fbiggest boost to pay and productivity
OL,14,Fin the workplace in a generation.
OL,16,FUnions warmly welcomed the measures as
OL,17,Fa "seismic shift" from the low pay,
OL,18,Flow productivity economy they accused
OL,19,Fthe previous Conservative government
OL,20,Fof presiding over.
