OL,3,CMillions of workers to get new rights
OL,4,Cfrom day one in job under new law
OL,6,FThere previously had been some
OL,7,Fwrangling by unions and businesses
OL,8,Fover the contents of the Bill, but the
OL,9,Fgovernment say they've struck a
OL,10,Fbalance between security for working
OL,11,Fpeople and flexibility for businesses.
OL,13,FThere are still a number of areas
OL,14,Fwhere tension remains, particularly
OL,15,Faround the definition of
OL,16,F"exploitative" zero-hour contracts,
OL,17,Fand the length of a probation period
OL,18,Fwhich would allow businesses to
OL,19,Fdismiss people "fairly".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
