OL,3,CMillions of workers to get new rights
OL,4,Cfrom day one in job under new law
OL,6,FMost of the reforms being put forward
OL,7,Fin the new law won't come into effect
OL,8,Ffor around two years - the government
OL,9,Fsay they will hold consultations on
OL,10,Fmany of the measures, and that some
OL,11,Fsecondary legislation will also need
OL,12,Fto be introduced as the Bill
OL,13,Fprogresses.
OL,15,FSome measures, such as the right to
OL,16,F"switch off" at the end of a working
OL,17,Fday, are not in the Bill but will be
OL,18,Fincluded in a so-called "Next Steps"
OL,19,Fdocument for further consideration and
OL,20,Fconsultation.
