OL,3,CMillions of workers to get new rights
OL,4,Cfrom day one in job under new law
OL,6,FWhen Labour first announced their
OL,7,Fflagship plan to reform worker's
OL,8,Frights, they promised to ban zero-hour
OL,9,Fcontracts entirely.
OL,11,FBut they later changed the wording of
OL,12,Fthat promise to only ban
OL,13,F"exploitative" zero-hour contracts, to
OL,14,Fthe frustration of many unions.
OL,16,FWorkers on those contracts will now be
OL,17,Fentitled to a "reasonable" number of
OL,18,Fshifts and financial compensation if a
OL,19,Fshift is cancelled or cut short.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
